# Sur Consulting — OpenOutreach UAE stack env  (DEFERRED — second account, later phase)
# Copy to uae.env and fill in only when you stand up the UAE account. NEVER commit the real uae.env.
#
# LLM (one model drives qualification + follow-up agent + search-keyword generation).
LLM_API_KEY=sk-REPLACE_ME
AI_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
LLM_API_BASE=https://api.anthropic.com/v1/

# --- Timezone ----------------------------------------------------------------
TZ=Asia/Dubai

# --- Egress / proxy (READ THIS) ----------------------------------------------
# 🔴 The app IGNORES HTTP_PROXY/HTTPS_PROXY (verified in source) — you CANNOT geo-locate this container
# to the UAE with an env var. A UAE account logging in from a US IP is a textbook restriction trigger,
# so to run this account safely you MUST give the container a real UAE egress by one of:
#   - running it on a UAE-located VPS (recommended), or
#   - routing the entire host through a UAE VPN (host-level, e.g. a wireguard/gluetun sidecar).
# Verify egress is AE before first login:  docker exec oo-uae sh -lc 'curl -s https://ipinfo.io/json'

# Host file ownership (container runs as uid 1000).
HOST_UID=1000
HOST_GID=1000

# Attach the account via cookie_data (Django Admin) the same way as US — see ops/phase0-checklist.md.
